The United States is a major producer of both biodiesel and bioethanol, in which the global production of bioethanol and biodiesel increases 4-folds from 35 to 135 billion liters from 2005 to 2016 (Rouhany and Montgomery, 2019). The production of biofuel in the U.S is saturated in the middle region with a significant increase of production (Fig. 4
                        ). In 2019, the biofuel consumption in the United States represented 7.3% of total transportation fuel consumption and is expected to increase over the coming years with the aid of government policies (US Energy Information Administration, 2020). The increase in production and demand of these biofuels was driven by Renewable Fuel Standard (RFS) program which was a federal policy implemented by US congress under the supervision of Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) as shown in Table 3
                         (Irwin et al., 2020).
